args:
On their way back to the royal city, the prince
and friends learn Alberia has been reborn as
the Dyrenell Empire. The prince has been
named traitor by the king—now the emperor—
and has no choice but to flee his pursuers.
After resting at King Alberius's castle,\nthe Halidom, and letting my wounds heal,\nI set off with the others for the royal city.
Though the mist had cleared, the road was\nlong. We passed through the Halidom's\npostern and followed along Myriage Lake.
The impostor who took Zethia and the Shard\nwould not leave my mind. Who WAS he?
I was certain my real father back at the royal\ncity knew the answer—and that he would help\nus get Zethia and the Shard back.
Blegh... Finally! We've nearly made it back\nto the royal city.
We have to hurry. Every moment we delay\nis a moment Zethia suffers.
Hold up. We got soldiers incoming.
Maybe a little welcomin' party for\n{player_name}?
I don't think so. That banner they're\nflying isn't Alberia's.
That's the banner of the Dyrenell Empire!\nBut how is that possible?
Prince {player_name}!\nThank the goddess I found you.
Leif? What are you doing here?\nDid something happen?
Ah, I feared word hadn't reached you yet.\nI'm sorry to bring this news to you,\nYour Highness, but...
Our land has been given a new name:\nthe Dyrenell Empire.
But that's the name of the evil empire\nthat was destroyed three centuries ago!
We're a kingdom, Leif, not an empire.\nTell me what happened.
He has abandoned our charter of peace\nand declared war on the rest of the world.
You cannot stay here, Your Highness.\nGet as far away as you can!
Leif, what are you so scared of?
Just hurry, before he finds you and—
Well, well. If it isn't Prince Miscreant\nin the flesh!
How fortunate for us to meet here.
I thought I'd have to scour the entire\nkingdom for you!
Who are you calling a miscreant, Harle?
Oh dear! Oh dear dear dear.\nHas no one warned you of the\nprecarious position you're in?
That sneer, that haughty bearing,\nthat way he keeps saying ＂dear...＂\nEverything about him turns my stomach.
State your point and be done with it, cur!\nWe've not time for the likes of you.
And for once, I agree with ya.\nThis guy's a chump and a half.
And YOU are all in the service of a\ncriminal, which makes you all complicit.
Of ALL of them! You unleashed fiends\non the royal city, you kidnapped dear,\ndear Princess Zethia—
Tell it to your cellmate; the two of you will\nhave SO very long to get acquainted.
Stop! This is a mistake!\nI demand to speak to my father!
Ha! That's never going to happen,\nyou stupid twit!
Sixth Heir to the Alberian Throne
Our father's the very one who\nordered me to take you in!
The man you think is Father is an impostor!\nOpen your eyes, Brother!
Ah-ah-ahhh! You're still talking,\nand criminals don't get to talk.\n...Guards! What are you waiting for?!
You metal-plated pond scum.\nHow dare you raise your weapons\nto your own prince!
Prince? All I see is a traitor.
And if the traitor is smart, he will lay\ndown his sword at once.
Listen to me, everybody: our only hope\nof figurin' this out is if we escape, so...\nRUUUUUUUN!
We have no choice. This way, everyone!
